    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured party evacuated to Noble Valiant drillship",
      "Examined by medic on drillship",
      "Consultation with onshore medical personnel",
      "Evacuated to shore for further evaluation",
      "BSEE investigation conducted"
    ],
    "summary": "On 27 September 2024, a Deckhand on the M/V Harvey Freedom support vessel injured his left leg during equipment back-loading operations from the Noble Valiant drillship. The injured party was positioned in the aft setback area attempting to steady a 50-foot basket with a tagline when the support vessel rolled, causing the worker to lose footing. The worker was wearing required PPE and working from the safe setback area. Sea conditions were 2-3 feet with occasional swells of 5-7 feet and winds of approximately 14 knots. The deck was wet but clear of other trip and slip hazards. The worker's boots were in serviceable condition with sufficient tread. The injury required surgery and resulted in more than 3 days lost time.",
    "recommendations": [],
